akas: North Woods Law: Die Wildlife-Ranger Germany
akas from release info: North Woods Law: Die Wildlife-Ranger Germany

401.title: And the Little Ones Too
401.plot: The discovery of a dead beaver in a Skowhegan parking lot leads Warden Parker on an exhaustive investigation involving surveillance cameras, anonymous informants and the assistance of the local police.

402.title: Above and Beyond
402.plot: For a game warden, there's no such thing as being "off the clock." Wardens McBrine and Carter embark on a multi-day hunt for a wanted man. Warden Herring investigates a mysterious shack on city property. Warden McKenney works to remove a deadly hazard from a river before a busy boating weekend.

403.title: Dirty Habits
403.plot: Parker investigates a rotting bear carcass that was dumped on the side of the road, leading him on a hunt across Maine to find a potential poacher. Blanchard catches a couple behaving badly on a wildlife refuge. Robertson rushes to the rescue of ducklings caught in a storm drain.

404.title: Truth Be Told
404.plot: The wardens encounter all types of people willing to stretch the truth to get out of hot water. Warden Parker searches for a trigger-happy shooter in a family neighborhood. Sergeant Spahr and Warden Lounder investigate a suspiciously shot turkey.

405.title: Catcher in the Wild
405.plot: A speeding dirt biker eludes Warden Robertson, but leaves a crucial clue to his whereabouts. Two dogs on the loose are chasing newborn deer. An ATV accident victim has an odd explanation for what caused his crash - it's up to Warden Lounder to find out if his story adds up.

406.title: Occupational Hazards
406.plot: Deep in the Maine woods, danger lurks behind every tree for the game wardens. Warden Herring comes across a sprawling illegal encampment on private property. Warden Stevens discovers three marijuana grows and must seize dozens of plants before the growers return.

407.title: In a Hot Second
407.plot: On land and water, it's the wardens' job to keep people safe. Warden McBrine coordinates a LifeFlight helicopter for the victim of a serious car crash. Warden Buuck spreads the word on boating safety. Warden Robertson checks some young anglers and makes a surprising discovery.

408.title: Close Encounters of the Wild Kind
408.plot: When Maine's wildlife wanders into human territory, it's game wardens to the rescue. Wardens Marquis and Fitzpatrick try to catch a dumpster-diving bear. A wily woodchuck gives Warden Lounder a run for his money. Warden Parker and son attempt a tricky beaver relocation.

409.title: Can't Believe Your Eyes
409.plot: Whether it's protecting wildlife or ensuring public safety, the Maine Game Wardens are on double duty during the summer. Warden Jeremy Judd tries to rescue a baby skunk in distress. Wardens MacCabe and Robertson investigate a stolen ATV that disappeared in the woods.

410.title: The Rescuers
410.plot: The wardens race against the clock to evacuate an injured hiker on the Appalachian Trail. A fishing license check leads Warden Dan Christianson to a stash of something suspicious. Things run afoul as Warden Kris MacCabe discovers Great Blue Herons are acting strangely - in two separate towns.

411.title: Long Shot
411.plot: Bird hunting season in Maine is in full swing. Simmons, Parker and Robertson catch sportsmen who fired from inside their truck. Spahr leads the search for a missing elderly woman in York County. The dive team is mustered to search for two duck hunters presumed drowned in the Sebasticook River.

412.title: Antlers and Antics
412.plot: Sergeant Spahr and Warden Lounder chase down a fleeing ATV. Warden Pelkey sends his K9 in search of evidence over a suspiciously shot moose. Warden MacCabe wrangles a tangled great blue heron. Warden Judd uses his keen instincts to guide a blind war veteran on a controlled moose hunt.

413.title: Weed It and Reap
413.plot: It's harvest season in Maine and the game wardens' busiest time of year. Warden Dudley helps an Amish family save their corn crop from a hungry bear. Wardens Carter and McBrine hunt for a man who's been hiding out in a cabin. And Sergeant Thrasher tries to find the grower of an illegal marijuana crop.

414.title: Excuses, Excuses
414.plot: Hunting season heats up and the wardens pull out the stops. Warden Herring calls in the air wing to track illegal activity on a game preserve. Warden Blanchard catches an intentional violator red-handed. Wardens Carter and McBrine execute a search warrant on a known poacher.

415.title: Dead Moose Talking
415.plot: The wardens wage a large-scale investigation into a moose that's been shot and left in the woods. A camouflaged ATV leads Warden Carleton Richardson to a convicted felon. Warden Kris MacCabe runs across a hunter unlike any other.

416.title: The Big Bad Woods
416.plot: Anything can happen in Maine's 17 million acres of rugged wilderness. Angry hunters get loud with Warden Lounder over an illegal deer. Warden MacCabe enlists a 90-year-old local to help catch a deer baiter. A missing hunter with Parkinson's sets off a full-scale search in difficult conditions.

417.title: Baiters Beware
417.plot: Fair chase - it's the gold standard of hunting, and in Maine, it's the law. Sgt. Simmons and Warden McKenney pursue a pair of brothers with bait piles. Warden Carter hunts for a father who may be teaching his son to poach. Warden Cross snares a trap thief.

418.title: Crossed Wires
418.plot: Even in the North Woods, communication is key - and sometimes the wardens have trouble getting their message through. McKenney and Robertson investigate a night hunting complaint. MacCabe tracks an illegal bear kill back to the source. K9 Tundra takes the lead in the search for a missing man.

419.title: Shifting Gears
419.plot: Deer season - even though it's the wardens' busiest time of year, they still have lots of other responsibilities on their plates. A stolen ATV steers Parker through a maze of suspects. Carter races to a domestic violence dispute. Marquis and Fitzpatrick set up a sting for a suspected night hunter.

420.title: In the Warden Wheelhouse
420.plot: In the final week of Maine's deer season, some hunters are desperate to bag a buck. Warden Robertson confronts a felon with an illegal gun and a pile of bait. Warden Buuck schools a hunter on the eighteen-hour law. Warden Carter investigates teen hunters terrorizing a neighborhood.

421.title: Homecoming
421.plot: The game wardens bring closure at long last to one of the most confounding mysteries in Maine Warden Service history and reflect on five years in the limelight with North Woods Law.

101.title: Warden Warriors
101.plot: The wardens use night vision technology to catch night hunters and poachers. Then, Warden LaFlamme must take matters into his own hands to protect the Maine public from a tragic outcome.

102.title: Moose Mania
102.plot: The MWS kicks into high gear as they search for poachers and crack down on dangerous activity with firearms. Warden MacCabe goes on a stake-out to bust "heater-hunters," people who hunt birds from the warmth of their trucks.

103.title: Off-Roadin'
103.plot: OFF-ROADIN': Two teams of Wardens join forces to bust ATV scofflaws and end up in a dramatic high-speed chase. Rookie Warden Kim Bates responds to a strange call: a report of a mysterious dead deer strung up by a chain deep in the back woods.

104.title: Gun Country
104.plot: GUN COUNTRY: During hunting season, nearly every person the Maine Game Wardens encounter is armed, and many are dangerous. One team of wardens investigate the shooting of a turkey hunter that could be an attempted homicide while another team sets up a stakeout.

105.title: On Thin Ice
105.plot: Hunters rush to stock up their freezers with deer, moose and bear meat for the long winter ahead. The wardens track a trail of blood to a man that may be poaching deer. The arrival of snow and ice sends the wardens into the back country for ice fishing.

106.title: Maine Freeze
106.plot: MAINE FREEZE: Things don't slow down in winter for the wardens, even in freezing temperatures. A team of wardens rush to the scene of a serious nighttime snowmobile accident, while another warden is on a stakeout for coyote poachers.

107.title: Wicked Summah
107.plot: Summer brings more than 20 million visitors every to Maine...and more people means more work for the Game Wardens. "Downeast", Sergeant Craven corners a runaway ATV and later must determine which of two double-crossing friends is telling the truth.

108.title: A Boat Load of Trouble
108.plot: It's summer in Vacationland. When the weather heats up the Maine Game Wardens head out on jet skis and speed boats to any of Maine's thousands of rivers or lakes to be sure everyone plays by the rules.

109.title: Harvest Time
109.plot: The end of summer is the busiest time of year for the Maine Warden Service, as the Wardens split their time patrolling the water and the woods. They're also on high-alert for criminals misusing the wilderness for illegal drug activity.

110.title: The Rookies
110.plot: Warden Miller and Sgt. Annis, come across a family with a surprising collection of weapons in their car and that same night encounter an odd ATV driver. Corporal Rick Clowery is on patrol in Maine's white water rivers.

111.title: Something's Afowl
111.plot: It's fall in Maine and waterfowl flock to that state.... and hunters are close behind. In southern Maine, wardens head into a wetland where they find hunters using illegal guns, ammo, and, drugs.

112.title: Racking Up the Bad Guys
112.plot: During moose season in Maine, sometimes family tradition... involves breaking the law. Sergeant Simmons investigates a murdered mother deer, while Warden Curtis and canine Cruizer search the backwoods of Downeast by moonlight to find a missing hunter.

113.title: The Crime of the Century
113.plot: Nothing riles up the Maine Game Wardens like poaching, and Sergeant Chris Simmons and a multi agency team search for the suspect of a heinous case of deer poaching.

114.title: Deer Deception
114.plot: Leaves fall off the trees, a chill is in the air and gun shots ring out across Maine Â- it's deer season, the most popular big game hunting season in the state.

115.title: Crossing the Line
115.plot: As snow falls and temperatures drop Wardens are watching the Canadian border for illegal hunting. Warden MacCabe helps catch nuisance wild turkeys with a rocket net.

116.title: Uncuffed!
116.plot: In the final episode of the season, North Woods Law looks back at the most pulse pounding stakeouts, hairiest animal encounters, and the biggest busts. Plus, a behind the scenes look at just what it takes to make a show about the Maine Game Wardens.

201.title: Ice Out
201.plot: The Maine Game Wardens search under the ice of a frozen lake for the victims of the worst snowmobile accident in recent history. The spring thaw brings all sorts of nuisance animal encounters, including skunks and bears. Warden MacCabe stakes out a wanted man who stole an owl.

202.title: Turkey Dogs
202.plot: Spring turkey hunting season has arrived and brings excited hunters into the woods. LaFlamme investigates a crime scene where someone may have poached a hen, and Spahr responds to a pit bull attack of a girl.

203.title: 24 Hours on the Job
203.plot: Spring is the busiest time of year...we follow several wardens round the clock for a busy 24 hours patrolling smelt poachers at night, tagging black bears with radio collars, searching for a home invader with a K9 team, and ending with a search and rescue for a lost girl in the woods on a rainy night.

204.title: Running Cold and Fast
204.plot: Mainers race to get their boats out on the water. A jet ski hit-and-run has the wardens searching for an elusive suspect with warrants for his arrest. A mysterious man arrives in Maine just after the Boston Marathon bombings and leaves a suicide note: an elaborate hoax or did he jump in the river?

205.title: Mud Season
205.plot: Spring rains bring lots of mud and Mainers are out getting their 4 wheelers dirty. The wardens investigate several accidents and rescue a boy caught in a flash flood. Parker investigates an ATV hit-and-run. A team of Maine wardens run in one of the toughest and muddiest mountain races in New England.

206.title: Summer Heats Up
206.plot: Summer is here and people are filling up the Maine woods and causing mayhem. MacCabe stumbles onto a disturbing campsite where the occupants may have vanished into thin air. The wardens search for a pot grow after a drug deal gone wrong. Blanchard has a string of hilarious animal encounters.

207.title: Mysteries in the Moose State
207.plot: Moose-mania sweeps the state and some of the wardens enter the annual moose-hunting lottery. After reports, Craven tracks down the mythical Maine mountain lion. The wardens are called in to find an elderly man lost in the woods. Curtis goes undercover in search of illegal marijuana growers.

208.title: Life on the Border
208.plot: Things are different way up in the North Woods along the Canadian border. A warden looking for smugglers encounters a drunk driver with a gun. A suicidal man enters the woods with a shotgun and law enforcement needs to find him.

209.title: Lost and Found
209.plot: A new class of wardens train for the most demanding part of their job: search and rescues. On the Appalachian Trail a hiker vanishes and the wardens lead one of largest search and rescue operations in Maine's history to find her.

210.title: Uncuffed 2
210.plot: We look back at the most exciting animal rescues, crime investigations and search and rescues of the first couple of seasons. The wardens celebrate North Woods Law day at a pro baseball game in Portland. Plus special unseen stories from this season.

211.title: Cheaters
211.plot: A notorious gang of poachers is up to their old tricks, the wardens stop some suspects from fleeing the state, and the forensic team investigates who shot at a woman in her backyard, nearly killing her.

212.title: Just One More...
212.plot: The rule is clear, one hunter one deer. But some hunters are greedy and the wardens are there to stop them. A deputy joins his first night hunting stakeout, LaFlamme searches for an arrow that can help solve a mystery, and a family covers up a crime.

213.title: The End Is Near
213.plot: A Facebook post leads the wardens to a gang of poachers, when the ringleader skips bail they embark on a manhunt. The wardens capture a flock of nuisance wild turkeys and search all night for a rabbit hunter lost in the snowy woods.

214.title: Throttle Out
214.plot: A sledder takes a jump that lands him in the hospital and the wardens investigate the crash. The wardens chase down a group of drunk snowmobilers. A strange pile of animal parts in the snow leads the wardens to a family of poachers.

215.title: Cold as Ice
215.plot: A smart phone with video evidence of a crime leads to a poacher. Two drunk sledders run over a warden and are chased through the woods. Herring hunts down a man that he knows with arrest warrants. LaFlamme helps a herd of deer in distress.

216.title: Moose on the Loose
216.plot: Teams use helicopters to radio-collar moose. The wardens rescue two skiers lost in the back country. A drunk sledder is caught and blames his nephew. A warden extinguishes a barn fire. A man with outstanding poaching warrants is arrested.

217.title: Take the Plunge
217.plot: The wardens are on full alert as the tourist season begins. A crowded campground is being terrorized by a fox. A rowdy partygoer gets a little irresponsible on an ATV.

218.title: All Hands On Deck
218.plot: When a boy goes missing the entire warden service turns out for a massive multi-day search effort. A second search for a lost hiker stretched the wardens to the limit .A stakeout of salmon poachers catches a pair in the act. A new K-9 is trained.

219.title: Night and Day
219.plot: Spring turkey hunting season and smelt runs have the wardens working night and day. Poached turkeys lead to a search warrant and stakeout for the suspects. Several animals are encountered including orphaned baby foxes, nuisance beavers, and a python. A team goes undercover to catch fish poachers.

220.title: 'Tis the Season
220.plot: Holiday season for the warden finds Pete Herring visiting a children's hospital in Portland with members of the K-9 unit; and Alan Curtis donating game to a soup kitchen. Meanwhile, Scott Thrasher invites everyone to his home for a potluck supper.

301.title: Outfoxed
301.plot: The start of the busy tourist season has the wardens out in full force. A dangerous fox is on the loose in a crowded campground-the wardens need to find it fast. An ATV rider appears to have been partying too hard and nearly causes a wipe out.

302.title: Man vs. Animal
302.plot: As winter melts into spring, all kinds of wildlife emerge, from baby raccoons to hungry black bears. A routine littering summons turns into a face off with a rabid pitbull. New evidence comes to light to revive an old deer poaching case.

303.title: Distress Call
303.plot: When the change in seasons brings warm weather in Maine, a game warden's job changes too. Sergeant Spahr helps a fledgling owl that has taken a tumble and Warden Stevens and a medical team hike into the night to locate a distressed hiker.

304.title: Trail of Trouble
304.plot: An ATV trail becomes the site of a high-speed chase when a man with an outstanding warrant attempts to flee from the Maine Warden Service. With the weather warming up, the wardens deal with intentional violators and serial offenders while enforcing laws.

305.title: Star Spangled Weekend
305.plot: Fourth of July is one of the biggest weekends of the year in Maine and crowds are out to celebrate. Warden Ryan Fitzpatrick and Caribou PD join forces when a group of fifty teens trash private property during a wild bonfire party.

306.title: Rapid Responders
306.plot: Water recreation season has the wardens out in full force. The Dive Team suits up to respond to an emeergency search and recovery call. An ATV rider with a camera on his helmet films his own crash. Undercover safety patrols lead to potential OUI busts.

307.title: High Jinks
307.plot: The wardens contend with illegal marijuana all across the state. Hidden in large tracts of land, and often protected by armed individuals, searching these illicit grow sites is dangerous work. An ATV crash involving three teens stumps the wardens.

308.title: Wild Kingdom
308.plot: Moose, bear and deer are what usually come to mind when thinking about Maine's wildlife, but sometimes, exotic animals make their way into the state. The wardens have to be prepared for any situation. Sergeant Spahr wrangles a Boa Constrictor.

309.title: Passing the Torch
309.plot: Warden Blanchard shows a high school student there is no such thing as a boring day on the job. Warden LaFlamme is promoted to Corporal of Landowner Relations and passes the responsibilities of his district on to Warden Lounder.

310.title: Hot on the Heels
310.plot: As hunting season winds down, the game wardens look out for overeager sportsmen bending the rules. Warden Fitzpatrick catches a Canadian hunter posing as an American. Wardens Parker and Buuck bring a fugitive night hunter to justice.

311.title: Takedown
311.plot: Maine's big game season attracts a flood of sportsmen who don't always play by the rules. The wardens watch for night hunters and track down a deer poacher. Some out-of-staters need a lesson in Maine hunting laws.

312.title: The Nick of Time
312.plot: At the start of hunting season in Maine, the wardens nab violators who are illegally illuminating wildlife, firing guns from their vehicles, and hunting over baited deer stands. Warden Lounder finds himself in a dangerous situation when he is surrounded.

313.title: Judgment Day
313.plot: Autumn in Maine keeps the wardens busy, as hunters head for the woods. Some sportsmen obey the rules; others try to evade them. Sergeant Simmons and Warden McKenney investigate a case about a poached moose.

314.title: Wild Moose Chase
314.plot: Fall brings the beginning of the great Maine moose season. Ride along with Warden MacCabe on his unbelievable six-day moose hunt. Wardens investigate a double moose kill, the granddaddy of wildlife crimes, and search for the source of mysterious shots.

315.title: Warden vs. Wild
315.plot: Game wardens are the guardians of Maine's natural resources and wildlife - and that means getting up close and personal with all kinds of animals. In this special episode, wardens relocate an angry black bear, rescue an orphaned baby moose and more.

316.title: Deer Detectives
316.plot: While the white tailed deer's numbers are dwindling due to lack of habitat and lack of feed. They are also the most preferred animal to hunt, which makes them more tempting to poachers - especially at night; A female hunter goes missing. A rescue team and command center is set up to for the search.

317.title: To Serve and Protect
317.plot: The game wardens are guardians of Maine's wildlife, but they also protect the public. Warden Carter must find an injured bear. A search is mounted for a missing man in the woods.

318.title: Down to the Wire
318.plot: A deer is found shot and killed in the middle of an empty field, surrounded by tyre tracks the officer's/trooper's attention; While a search warrant has been issued on the home of a convicted felon, in hopes of obtaining evidence of illegal hunting and/or any firearms - which convicted felon's are not allowed to possess; A man shoots and kills a deer from his pick-up truck, which just happens to be only yards away from occupied residential buildings;

imdb.plot outline: Animal Planet green-lights NORTH WOODS LAW, a new, six-part reality series that follows Maine's elite game warden service, set to premiere this March. This patrol unit navigates the Pine Tree State's rugged terrain during hunting season - one of the busiest and most perilous times of the year. Each punch of the time clock is a ticket to extreme danger and drama as undercover stings and intense rescues are all in a day's work. Whether they're tracking bears on dangerous mountains or busting drunk drivers on ATVs, these wardens risk life and limb to protect animals and serve the people of Maine.
imdb.title: North Woods Law
plot: Danger and drama are around every bend for Maine's elite game wardens, who are followed in this series as they navigate the state's rugged terrain during a busy and risk-filled hunting season.

This patrol unit navigates the Pine Tree State's rugged terrain during hunting season - one of the busiest and most perilous times of the year. Each punch of the time clock is a ticket to extreme danger and drama as undercover stings and intense rescues are all in a day's work. Whether they're tracking bears on dangerous mountains or busting drunk drivers on ATVs, these wardens risk life and limb to protect animals and serve the people of Maine.::Animal Planet's press release, January 2012
